References: BID:65227   |   URL:http://www.securityfocus.com/bid/65227   |   CISCO:20140128 Cisco Identity Services Engine HTTP Control Interface for NAC Web Agent Cross-Site Scripting Vulnerability   |   URL:http://tools.cisco.com/security/center/content/CiscoSecurityNotice/CVE-2014-0680   |   CONFIRM:http://tools.cisco.com/security/center/viewAlert.x?alertId=32617   |   OSVDB:102588   |   URL:http://osvdb.org/102588   |   SECTRACK:1029701   |   URL:http://www.securitytracker.com/id/1029701   |   SECUNIA:56672   |   URL:http://secunia.com/advisories/56672

Name: CVE-2014-0681
Description: Cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability in Cisco Identity Services Engine (ISE) 1.2 patch 2 and earlier allows remote attackers to inject arbitrary web script or HTML via a report containing a crafted URL that is not properly handled during generation of report-output pages, aka Bug ID CSCui15064.
References: BID:65183   |   URL:http://www.securityfocus.com/bid/65183   |   CISCO:20140128 Cisco Identity Services Engine Reports Output Cross-Site Scripting Vulnerability   |   URL:http://tools.cisco.com/security/center/content/CiscoSecurityNotice/CVE-2014-0681   |   CONFIRM:http://tools.cisco.com/security/center/viewAlert.x?alertId=32609   |   OSVDB:102589   |   URL:http://osvdb.org/102589   |   SECTRACK:1029699   |   URL:http://www.securitytracker.com/id/1029699   |   SECUNIA:56714   |   URL:http://secunia.com/advisories/56714

Name: CVE-2014-0682
Description: Cisco WebEx Meetings Server allows remote authenticated users to bypass authorization checks and (1) join arbitrary meetings, or (2) terminate a meeting without having a host role, via a crafted URL, aka Bug ID CSCuj42346.
References: BID:65198   |   URL:http://www.securityfocus.com/bid/65198   |   CISCO:20140128 Cisco WebEx Meetings Server Unauthorized Meeting Actions Vulnerability   |   URL:http://tools.cisco.com/security/center/content/CiscoSecurityNotice/CVE-2014-0682   |   CONFIRM:http://tools.cisco.com/security/center/viewAlert.x?alertId=32618   |   OSVDB:102590   |   URL:http://osvdb.org/102590   |   SECTRACK:1029700   |   URL:http://www.securitytracker.com/id/1029700   |   SECUNIA:56668   |   URL:http://secunia.com/advisories/56668

Name: CVE-2014-0683
Description: The web management interface on the Cisco RV110W firewall with firmware 1.2.0.9 and earlier, RV215W router with firmware 1.1.0.5 and earlier, and CVR100W router with firmware 1.0.1.19 and earlier does not prevent replaying of modified authentication requests, which allows remote attackers to obtain administrative access by leveraging the ability to intercept requests, aka Bug IDs CSCul94527, CSCum86264, and CSCum86275.
References: CISCO:20140305 Cisco Small Business Router Password Disclosure Vulnerability   |   URL:http://tools.cisco.com/security/center/content/CiscoSecurityAdvisory/cisco-sa-20140305-rpd   |   EXPLOIT-DB:45986   |   URL:https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/45986/

Name: CVE-2014-0684
Description: Cisco NX-OS 6.2(2) on Nexus 7000 switches allows local users to cause a denial of service via crafted sed input, aka Bug ID CSCui56136.
References: CISCO:20140505 Cisco Nexus 7000 Denial of Service Vulnerability   |   URL:http://tools.cisco.com/security/center/content/CiscoSecurityNotice/CVE-2014-0684   |   CONFIRM:http://tools.cisco.com/security/center/viewAlert.x?alertId=34131

Name: CVE-2014-0685
Description: Cisco Nexus 1000V InterCloud 5.2(1)IC1(1.2) and earlier for VMware allows remote attackers to bypass ACL deny statements via crafted (1) IGMPv2 or (2) IGMPv3 packets, aka Bug ID CSCug61691.
References: CISCO:20140505 Cisco Nexus 1000V Access Control List Bypass Vulnerability   |   URL:http://tools.cisco.com/security/center/content/CiscoSecurityNotice/CVE-2014-0685   |   CONFIRM:http://tools.cisco.com/security/center/viewAlert.x?alertId=34130

Name: CVE-2014-0686
Description: Cisco Unified Communications Manager (aka Unified CM) 9.1 (2.10000.28) and earlier allows local users to gain privileges by leveraging incorrect file permissions, aka Bug IDs CSCul24917 and CSCul24908.
References: BID:65281   |   URL:http://www.securityfocus.com/bid/65281   |   CISCO:20140131 Cisco Unified Communications Manager Operating System-Level Privilege Escalation Vulnerability   |   URL:http://tools.cisco.com/security/center/content/CiscoSecurityNotice/CVE-2014-0686   |   CONFIRM:http://tools.cisco.com/security/center/viewAlert.x?alertId=32683   |   OSVDB:102750   |   URL:http://osvdb.org/102750   |   SECUNIA:56818   |   URL:http://secunia.com/advisories/56818   |   XF:cisco-ucm-cve20140686-priv-esc(90852)   |   URL:https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/vulnerabilities/90852
